Constructor -->
-> is a block(similar to method) having same name as that of class name
-> does not have any return-type, not even void.
-> The only modifiers applicable for Constructor are public, protected, default and private
-> It executes automatically when we create an object.

Use Of Constructor:
Constructor is used to initilize an object

Types of Constructor:
1. Default Constructor (no-arg constructor) -> Create By Compiler 
2. No-arg Constructor (User-defined) -> Create by Programmer
3. Parameterized Constructor -> Create by Programmer
